Subject: Re:[T2] Cylinder 3 Exhaust Burnout Help.

Greg, this is not a burned valve, it must be a broken part 
(valve/spring/guide/valve seat)
Remove the valve cover and look carefully at the #3 rocker assembly! Is it loose, 
very loose, broken. Remove this one (rocker) and see if the spring is loose or broken.

How do you know that #3 is not firing?

Get under that bus and check everything, including push rod, and pushrod tube.

Let us know, Ben
http://www.desert2002.com/heads.htm 

